ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This course teaches you the ethics of research and how to avoid making mistakes by thinking through experiments and considering all of your options before you begin them. I would recommend the course to all students.
This is mandatory. But it is actually very useful for graduate students who need to conduct experiments
ENAS 508 was a fairly standard responsible conduct of research type class. I would recommend it if the student has not taken another similar class.
It is a class that gives a general overview of ethics related to science such as publications and etc.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course helped me a lot and will continue to provide advice for my research going forward.
This course ensured that I understood the proper research conduct requirements for scientific studies.
It definitely did give me information on things that I would not have learned anywhere.
